name: Begu Ganjang
description:
13. Begu Ganjang
Begu Ganjang, means ‘long(tall) ghost’. this mystical creatures used to be harmless and used by villagers to protect rice field and farms. slowly their purpose changes drastically to harm people by the order of their owner. 

a part of my Inktober serial Illustrations titled ‘Indonesian Horror Stories’. 

thank you!
